[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man who died after car hit wall in Dundonald crash named

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man who died after his car crashed into a wall in Ayrshire at the weekend has been named by police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Brian Dewhirst, aged 32, was driving the Vauxhall Astra when the collision took place on the A759 near Dundonald at about 17:40 on Saturday.
His passengers - two men aged 24 and 25 - were seriously injured and were taken to Crosshouse Hospital in Kilmarnock.
Police have appealed for anyone who saw the crash to come forward with information.
